{"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"A data type that describes the state of a confirmation dialog that can be shown to the user. The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Action","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" generic is the type of actions that can be sent from tapping on a button in the sheet.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ConfirmationDialogState","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Action","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This type can be used in your application’s state in order to control the presentation or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dismissal of dialogs. It is preferable to use this API instead of the default SwiftUI API for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dialogs because SwiftUI uses 2-way bindings in order to control the showing and dismissal of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dialogs, and that does not play nicely with the Composable Architecture. The library requires"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that all state mutations happen by sending an action so that a reducer can handle that logic,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which greatly simplifies how data flows through your application, and gives you instant"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"testability on all parts of your application."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use this API, you model all the dialog actions in your domain’s action enum:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["enum Action: Equatable {","  case cancelTapped","  case deleteTapped","  case favoriteTapped","  case infoTapped","","  \/\/ Your other actions","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And you model the state for showing the dialog in your domain’s state, and it can start off in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" state:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct State: Equatable {","  var confirmationDialog: ConfirmationDialogState<AppAction>?","","  \/\/ Your other state","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, in the reducer you can construct a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ConfirmationDialogState"},{"type":"text","text":" value to represent the dialog"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you want to show to the user:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["func reduce(into state: inout State, action: Action) -> EffectTask<Action> {","  switch action {","  case .cancelTapped:","    state.confirmationDialog = nil","    return .none","","  case .deleteTapped:","    state.confirmationDialog = nil","    \/\/ Do deletion logic...","","  case .favoriteTapped:","    state.confirmationDialog = nil","    \/\/ Do favoriting logic","","  case .infoTapped:","    state.confirmationDialog = ConfirmationDialogState(","      title: \"What would you like to do?\",","      buttons: [","        .default(TextState(\"Favorite\"), action: .send(.favoriteTapped)),","        .destructive(TextState(\"Delete\"), action: .send(.deleteTapped)),","        .cancel(),","      ]","    )","    return .none","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And then, in your view you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"confirmationDialog(_:dismiss:)"},{"text":" method on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to present the dialog in a way that works best with the Composable Architecture:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Button(\"Info\") { viewStore.send(.infoTapped) }","  .confirmationDialog(","    self.store.scope(state: \\.confirmationDialog),","    dismiss: .cancelTapped","  )"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This makes your reducer in complete control of when the dialog is shown or dismissed, and makes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it so that any choice made in the dialog is automatically fed back into the reducer so that you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can handle its logic.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Even better, you can instantly write tests that your dialog behavior works as expected:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let store = TestStore(","  initialState: Feature.State(),","  reducer: Feature()",")","","store.send(.infoTapped) {","  $0.confirmationDialog = ConfirmationDialogState(","    title: \"What would you like to do?\",","    buttons: [","      .default(TextState(\"Favorite\"), send: .favoriteTapped),","      .destructive(TextState(\"Delete\"), send: .deleteTapped),","      .cancel(),","    ]","  )","}","store.send(.favoriteTapped) {","  $0.confirmationDialog = nil","  \/\/ Also verify that favoriting logic executed correctly","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SwiftUI"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/confirmationdialogstate"]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ConfirmationDialogState\/init(title:message:buttons:)","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ConfirmationDialogState\/init(ti